{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_87","type":"agent_message","text":"Implemented the prompt 15 event/audit layer end to end. The backend now has a typed event taxonomy in [events.py](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/models/events.py), an append/read repository in [events.py](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/repositories/events.py), a higher-level logging service in [event_log.py](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/services/event_log.py), and `SessionService` wiring in [sessions.py](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/services/sessions.py) so session creation and stage transitions emit durable, versioned events and update `last_event_id` pointers on affected stage snapshots. I also documented the taxonomy in [event-taxonomy.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/event-taxonomy.md) and wrote the required reviewer summary in [15-event-log-and-audit-trail.summary.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/prompts/15-event-log-and-audit-trail.summary.md).\n\nVerification: `pytest backend/tests/test_event_log_service.py backend/tests/test_session_service.py` passed (`10 passed`), `pytest backend/tests` passed (`36 passed`), and `ruff check backend/app backend/tests` passed. No browser checks or screenshots were run because this prompt only changed backend/domain code. I made a checkpoint commit for the implementation as `9ca7cc4` (`feat(prompt-15): event log and audit trail`)."}}
